    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Wash, then add your <strong>spinach</strong> to a colander and pour <strong>boiled water</strong> all over it so that it starts to wilt</p><p>Rinse the<strong> wilted spinach</strong> under <strong>cold running water</strong> until it's cool</p><p>Once cool, squeeze as much water out of the spinach as you can, then chop it roughly</p><p>Chop your <strong>dill </strong>finely, including the stalks</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "media": {
